    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A type of full, baggy knickerbocker, typically worn for field sports, especially golf. The name connotes the length of the pants leg that extends 4 inches below the knee. These were popularized in the 1920s and remained in fashion until the late 1930s.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
